Yokogawa Electric Rises Most in a Month After Brokerage Upgrade

-- B y   J a s o n   C l e n f i e l d
-- 
2011-03-09T03:33:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/yokogawa-electric-rises-most-in-a-month-after-brokerage-upgrade.html
  Yokogawa Electric Corp. (6841)  climbed the
most in a month in Tokyo trading after Mizuho Securities Co.
boosted its rating on the maker of electronic measuring tools to
“outperform” from “underperform.”  Tokyo-based Yokogawa rose 7.8 percent at the 11 a.m.
trading break on the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the biggest gain
since Feb. 7. The benchmark Nikkei 225 Stock Average gained 1
percent.  Shares of Yokogawa also got a boost after a report Japanese
machinery orders rose more than economists expected in January,
signaling manufacturers plan to boost investment. Bookings for
equipment, an indicator of  capital spending  in three to six
months, increased 4.2 percent from December, when they rose 1.7
percent, the Cabinet Office said today in Tokyo.  Orders were projected to have climbed 3 percent, according
to the median forecast of 28 economists surveyed by Bloomberg
News.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jason Clenfield in Tokyo at 
